               <head>Certificate; Frostenden, etc.; 1408, etc.</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> Certificate of <persName>
                           <forename>Peter</forename> 
                           <surname>Schelton</surname>, LL.B., commissary of
                  <persName>
                              <forename>Alexander</forename>, bp. of <placeName role="bishop" type="diocese" key="place_101090">Norwich</placeName>
                           </persName></persName>, 
                  that at a visitation held 24 November, <origDate when="1408">1408</origDate>, in the parish church of
                  <placeName key="place_105296">Frostenden</placeName>, the  <orgName key="org_104030">abbot and convent of Sybeton</orgName> 
                  pro<pb n="522"/>duced evidences of the appropriation of the church of 
                  <placeName key="place_105526">Sibton (Sybeton)</placeName> with the chapel of <placeName key="place_105453">Peasenhall (Pesenhale)</placeName> annexed,
                  and also of the appropriation of the churches of <placeName key="place_105464">Rendham</placeName>,
                  <placeName key="place_105249">Cransford (Cranisford)</placeName>, <placeName key="place_105560">Westleton</placeName>, and <placeName key="place_105542">Tunstall</placeName>,
                  and repeated at a visitation held in <placeName key="place_105172">Beccles ("Bekkelys")</placeName> church 
                  <origDate when="1413-06-18">18 June, 1413</origDate>. 
                  [Original of the first.]
                  </p>
